         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper, we study the number of zeros of the equation &lt;tex-math&gt;$X^e_1 + X^e_2 + \cdots + X^e_n \equiv 0 (\operatorname{mod} p)$&lt;/tex-math&gt;, where &lt;latex&gt;$e &gt; 1$&lt;/latex&gt; is a positive integer and &lt;tex-math&gt;$p \equiv 1 (\operatorname{mod} e)$&lt;/tex-math&gt; is a prime. For e = 5, 7, we compute the recurrence satisfied by these numbers, using the generalized Jacobi sums.</p>
          </abstract>
